reviews: Maison Breguet is small and perfectly formed! An elegant boutique hotel providing stylish environment throughout, warm, friendly and efficient service with little luxurious extras. The location is fantastic in the bustling neighbourhoods of La Marais and Bastille with the best atmosphere, bars, cafes, bistros, shop galore and a Sunday market. 2 minutes from the Metro. Walking about is easy and only a short walk on to Île St Louis and beyond. The bedrooms were very comfortable and we were amazed at the silence at night with windows open. Highly recommend. Wouldn’t hesitate to book again. Good value.

- Most of the time no one at reception, this is basic 5 star requirement
- calls not answered for a lot of the time. along with the phone ringing over the required 10 rings.
- late food a few times (ordered from outside). latest 15 minutes. not okay.
- friendly female worker with short hair. She knew how to answer the phone, quick with food, and very helpful.
- work done in rooms is poor.
- Flush is not working right for both room toilets (had to move three times!)
- vegan snacks in mini bar and drinks. Great.
- no rubber seal for the shower, all some how removed? not put back on? confusing
- Staines on rug
- no towel hangers
- Two face clothes the first time. Then not the second time. I could go on about housekeeping. They’re just not good at what they do.
- Having to go into a cheap low end hotel for the car park is ridiculous.
- having a nap, yoga, rest and just chill time was impossible due to housekeeping slamming doors, loud talking, loud laughing and they seem to take ages in the same rooms. I watched and one time it was in and out of one room for almost an hour
- took 45 minutes to do the room I was in before the final room. manager said due to the dog. that’s not true. just excuses.
- a worker was intense wanting to touch my dog. I said no and she said “what’s wrong!!” very odd. I don’t want you touching my dog and it was very intense how she went about it. freaked my dog out. no nice.
- I have a 16 room home and they find an hour cleaning a room (small) normal.
- my items got move by housekeeping
- Had British chavs to either side of us. awful. Slamming of doors, their accents, the way they were. was intense.
- water in and out of hot to cold. the manager swore the water was “fine for me” yeah sure…that’s a big lie. a bath full of cold water. yeah…nice! they need to sort out there water problem. I swear no maintenance person came. but if they did…get rid of them.

there’s so much more that went wrong.

Worse time was when my partner Rang asking about food again and got “yes! Ma’am I’m bringing it to you”. While it actually been my partner. Would he have spoken to a male like that. Seemed like he was very bothered. I’m paying for service, yet it’s slacking at times. Mostly Monday it was slacking. I brought it up to him as I was so taken back and he just kept making up excuses. His story changed so much. I don’t want to hear about customers, or how busy you may have been or whatever truth or lie. I’m a guest. I deserve great service. Otherwise someone needs to tell whoever the hotel needs more staff. And if it isn’t possible. Something needs to change. Because it isn’t fair on others to just wait and wait. My partner had him also when my partner wanted a drink, talking and b**ching about me to my fiancée. My partner asked for two drinks, and this guy spiralled on about me. I get that he is like that due to his certain book he reads. My partner told me what was said. He also made up the whole thing and my partner said…I was there I heard it. My partner also had to just go get the drinks himself and this guy was craz*. I was just angry by what I heard. How dare he. He was annoyed his thought the person in the line was a woman. I can guess why he doesn’t like women. I can easily guess he finds men above women for a certain reason…we know what that is. To hear he’s talking nonsense about me to my partner is very unprofessional and disgraceful. I know he doesn’t have respect for females. I know why and he knows why that is, a certain book. I get other males he’s around don’t respect women. Don’t care to treat women well. He’s used to seeing women as below him. He sees women as below men. And people not part of a certain thing nudge nudge…that anyone not a part of a certain thing are below too. the thing you know…no proof, no evidence, and another thing out of 1000s of others people believe. Such a weird world and a poiso* of the world.

Located between 3rd and 11th arrondissement, it is the best place for people who enjoy the best bistros and (natural) wine bars of the city. Several metro stations are in 5 mins walking distance and a Sunday market across the street.
It is our second visit to Maison Breguet and we can recommend it as a very clean, cosy place and friendly service. Also the breakfast can be recommended

My fav hotel in Paris. Very nice design. Location is great - not touristic, but quite close to everything you want to see. A lot of good restaurants. Highly recommended.

Staff is very friendly and helpful.

My husband, daughter and I had the most incredible few days at Maison Breguet. From the moment we arrived until the moment we (sadly) left we felt right at home. Staff were all incredibly warm and helpful. (Big thank you to Francois!) The room was absolutely perfect. Stef made the best drinks we’ve had and was so wonderful to talk to. We truly can’t say enough wonderful things about our experience! Thanks to all who made our stay so special - we will definitely be back!!

A outstanding small hotel with a world class personalised service. I will never select another hotel in Paris. Thank you for making our stay an fantastic experience and especially a big thank you to the best concierge that ensured we visited the best places in Paris

We had a wonderful trip to Paris made all the better by our stay at Maison Breguet. The staff are all wonderful and provided great help prior to and during our visit. The hotel itself is immaculate and really well situated in a lovely area, close to all the sights.

Fabulous long weekend at the hotel after nearly 3 years of Pandemic changes etc.. the hotel is perfect, we stayed in deluxe room 409 and the only thing I would recommend is that a proper shower is installed, other than that the hotel and everything about our stay was perfect. The location is brilliant, the breakfast food was really good and the staff are lovely and friendly..

This is a pleasant place to stay but it’s certainly not 5 star in our opinion, the room (superior!) was more like an upmarket Premier Inn and if we were paying Premier Inn prices we would have been very happy. However at over €900 for 2 nights, we felt exploited.
The breakfast room, also the restaurant, and the breakfast itself were good as was the service.

Staff were really friendly and helpful rooms were clean and well equipped.food and drink all excellent, would definitely recommend for couples or families. Metro is 5 minute walk.
Spa is small but really nice.

Maison Bréguet was ideal. Quiet, relaxing, comfortable and situated at the heart of the very cool La Marais neighbourhood. The rooms are spacious, comfy and beautifully decorated. The pool and spa area is clean and peaceful, great for a relaxing afternoon.

The restaurant and cocktail bar serve amazing food and drinks, and all the staff are kind and attentive. They did all they could to make sure we had the best possible stay. I'd recommend this place very highly - was perfect for our trip.

From the beginning to end Maison Brequet was perfect. Best hotel staff!! This is more than a “Boutique” hotel in Bastille. The place is simple chic, with a cool vibe which was awesome for weekend trips.

We use to own an apartment near this hotel and since selling it we have stayed in several venues in the same area and the Marais. Maison Breguet is a great upscale boutique hotel with a lovely bar and restaurant area in an ideal location to explore Paris. There is also a full spa and pool which we did not try on this visit. We had booked a deluxe room though we were upgraded on arrival to a junior suite which had a nice seating area as well as a great bed. The hotel is so quiet at night it made sleeping easy. All the staff we encountered were friendly and helpful with Francois very welcoming on arrival. The hotel is close to Bastille metro so handy for several metro lines including line one. Any gripes - not really - we prefer a walk in shower so would request this next time. Do we recommend this hotel - yes. Will we stay again - yes.

Sonia and Fiona and the team has been excellent to us in our stay! They gave us great suggestions on where to eat in the area, and took special care to find items that we misplaced in the hotel.
Most of all, we were engaged during the stay, and they surprised us by sending a bottle of bubbly to our room with their compliments! Merci, Merci, Merci !

We will definitely make Maison Breguet our Paris home away from home in the future!

We visited Paris for only five days,
Our hotel was splendid in myriad ways.
The staff were so friendly and amenable,
Je crois que le mot est ‘incroyable!’.

We started each day with sauna and swim,
‘Cuisine Parisienne’… the need to keep trim.
Our room was deluxe with a bed magnifique,
Garantie de notre sejour romantique.

Located near Place de la Bastille,
Le Marais alive and extremely gentille.
For a brilliant time you’ll never forget,
Book yourself into the Maison Breguet!

Had a wonderful stay. Beautiful, spacious junior suite with private balcony. Ours had an opaque door to the bathroom - some junior suites have clear glass doors to the bathroom. Plenty of clothing storage but it was in the bathroom and exposed to the steam; not a problem for a few days stay. Second storage area in the sitting area was great for our daughter's things. Quick and accommodating room service.
A little strange to walk through the bar/restaurant to access the rear elevator but we got used to it pretty quickly. It was so nice to be greeted by the staff as we walked through - - they treated us like old friends. Phenomenal hotel staff in general - - everyone was so welcoming, kind, and helpful. Going above and beyond to help us navigate the French transportation system for our day trips and great restaurant suggestions. Special shout-out to Francois, Celine and Stefan. You all made our trip to Paris so perfect!

Our family recently stayed at Hotel Maison Bréguet Paris for 5 nights and it was an incredible experience.

The staff was so friendly and welcoming and assisted us with anything we needed...you really get the sense that they want you to have a wonderful time during your stay. We are family of 4 – two adults and two kids and having ability to stay with adjoined rooms with wonderful queen size beds was a great find.

The hotel is very clean, located in very close walking proximity to anything you need. There are many cozy cafeterias in the neighborhood to enjoy breakfast with fresh croissant and coffee as well as places to have lunch or dinner.

One thing I’ll remember forever is the best hot shower with good water pressure 😊something that makes tourist life so much better after long day under burning Paris sun while visiting dozens of tourist’s attractions.

On behalf of all members of my family I want to say THANK YOU to Hotel Maison Bréguet Paris team for making our Paris experience so memorable.

Stunning boutique hotel in a lovely neighborhood close to Marais. Gorgeous decor with a very cool vibe and super comfy beds.

All staff are great but a special mention to Fred and Fiona who were so helpful and kind. I am with my daughters (8 and 11) but would love to come back with my partner.

The hotel also has a spa area with a small pool, sauna and steam room. It’s immaculate.

Lastly there is a beautiful outdoor patio which we sat on every night as the weather was great.

Great hotel…

Dear Francois and Fiona,
I just wanted to thank you both for the special care you took during our stay at Maison Breguet, especially organising the wheelchair and the disabled-accessible room and shower for me. Thank you so much for your kindness and hospitality. We will definitely be back! Merci!
Very best wishes,
Nicola

The hotel had a cool and cozy decor. The staff was VERY professional and friendly! The location was great! A quiet street but very close to key-Metrostation taking you anywhere in minutes.
Unfortunately the hotel-bar was closed. It looked cool... The room was spacious and light and very clean.

Rooms are absolutely tiny, even at the “superior” level. You feel cramped, claustrophobic and nauseous. You will hit your shins a lot. There is no space for suitcase or for any of your belongings.

The food is disappointing although looks good. Breakfast rather bland, fresh orange juice watered down.

There is a suite spa / sauna / plunge pool. The gym is not worth the space. The elliptical squeaks and the whole space is probably less than 150 sq ft.

Location is also a bit so so.

Your staff were exceptional, polite, attentive and friendly. Always willing to assist with our enquires. We had dinner the 1st night at hotel as we were jet lagged in the beautiful courtyard garden . My margarita was authentic and delicious and the recommended Rose was excellent. Thank you for making our stay in Paris a success.

I selected this hotel because of its location but it was a disaster. On arrival there was actually No one in reception on a supposedly 5 star hotel?? My room was not ready. Asking tfor a recommendation to have lunch close by while waiting, they send us to the worst meal of our trip!
Lastly they charge me twice! And after 2 weeks I haven't receive my money back. Please save yourself headaches and dont come here.

I was so impressed by this gem of a hotel! Most notably was the spa and gym area that were very high end. The rooms are perfectly clean and the staff so kind with all our needs and desires. I recommend this hotel for anyone who wishes to see Paris from a more genuine angle, with closeness to the Marais and the Latin Quarter.

We had a wonderful time at this lovely hotel and can’t wait to go back. Lovely neighbourhood, helpful staff, yummy food, really nice, clean and comfy rooms. We are so glad we chose an independent hotel rather than a corporate chain. Brilliant for families with kids too - we booked two interconnecting rooms and it was really perfect.

We had a fantastic stay at the hotel. Great location and to explore Paris with our children (14 & 11). Great hotel - v comfortable and enjoyable stay. Staff were friendly and very helpful. Would highly recommend and we would certainly stay again when visiting Paris

We stayed in one of their Superior rooms with a full ceiling of windows and it was incredible. With a retractable awning, we were able to make the space dark and cozy for sleeping, and during the day we could see clouds, birds, and even a thunderstorm from our room. Everything was nicely appointed (Maison Margiela toiletries and a lovely Nespresso machine in the room) and it was a very comfortable retreat.

The bar + restaurant downstairs are stunning, we sat in the courtyard for lunch and it was so lovely and peaceful. Every detail is thought of in the common spaces and it was hard to actually want to leave as it was just such a chic and comfortable space.

It's situated in a great area with easy walking and so much to see. Highly recommend!

Maison Bréguet is a delightful gem of a hotel, conveniently located near the Place de la Bastille yet tucked away on a quiet street away from the animated nearby street life. I loved the fact that all the major tourist attractions were within easy reach by foot or via the nearby Metro stations yet far enough off the beaten path to feel like I was staying in a non-touristy Parisian neighborhood. I found my room to be large by Paris hotel standards, immaculately clean, and very comfortable. The front desk staff was excellent, to a fault they were all warm, welcoming and exceptionally competent. A special mention for Francois who went above and beyond to be be helpful. I highly recommend the hotel restaurant too, the food was quite good and they have a beautiful outdoor courtyard in the back.

Great hotel, great location with lots of good bars and restaurants, just 7 min walk from Place des Vosges / the Marais , rooms were very clean , stuff at the reception were very friendly and efficient specially Fiona, very good breakfast with great service.,

Excellent Boutique hotel. Quiet and central location. Very good staff and excellent service and breakfast.
The SPA is and extra plus.

The hotel is beautifully designed and has a very nice atrium seating and also a courtyard.

We loved maison breguet, the staff were so friendly and helpful and the decor was extremely well done. Some beautiful little details in the room and restaurant. Food at the restaurant was first class. Overall, a gem of a place. Well done team!

Loved it. Maison Breguet is design-forward yet warm and welcoming. Superb staff. Delicious food. I was pleased with my room and the overall environment of the property. I liked it so much that I had trouble leaving and continued to work on my laptop in the restaurant.

What can I say. We adored this hotel from start to finish of our stay. We arrived in Paris and was greeted with the warmest of welcomes by Francois on reception.

We were staying at the hotel for 5 days for my birthday Celebrations. Francois took
The time to ask the reason for our stay on our check in and surprised us with organising birthday cake and fresh fruit to be waiting for us in the room.

Francois organised all of our taxi requirements and
couldn't have been more helpful.

The bar staff were knowledgeable and friendly,
especially a young girl I believe her name was
Amelle or Amarelle? (Apologies if I've got this wrong)
however she was really lovely and chatted to us
about local restaurants and gave us recommendations for night life whilst eating dinner.

The hotel rooms were spotless with modem
amenities. We had a beautiful room with a balcony
overlooking the courtyard.

The spa was immaculate and all in all we couldn’t
recommend this hotel enough.
We will look forward to returning again in the future

A truly lovely hotel with brilliant staff and fabulous service. They made our stay in Paris (in the snow and rain!) amazing. We loved everything about the place. Breakfast with Armelle and Julie was outstanding. They really looked after our girls and so were a big hit! with us! Even when Julie was away, her deputy was just as brilliant making sure he helped us in any way he could.
I cannot fault them. It was the loveliest experience and we will definitely come back!

Stayed for 2 nights at the hotel with my daughter. We loved it. The service was fantastic, the bed was the most comfortable bed I have ever slept in and the restaurant was great. Will definitely be back.

We stayed for 5 nights at Maison Breguet. The rooms are peaceful and comfortable but the highlights of this hotel are the food - which was consistently excellent across breakfast and dinner - and the staff who are attentive, friendly and welcoming. This is very much a boutique hotel but one with equivalent facilities to that of a large five star property and with an inclusive approach towards families and children. It’s also very stylish as you would expect in this part of Paris. One minor criticism is that food options outside of restaurant meal times are a little limited.

The staffs are extremely nice and helpful! I asked them to help me set up the room as a surprise for my friend's birthday. And the staffs were all so helpful! The hotel is new and the location is convenient. Would definitely recommend!

This is a real gem, a place to enjoy and relax, strategically located for Le Marais but on the edgy side of the 11th. Facilities are superb, staff is friendly and helpful, and the restaurant is a destination in itself. Looking forward to go back soon ..,

My wife and I stayed here for 4 nights in February. It is a great hotel with great, helpful staff. The room and bathroom are spotlessly cleaned everyday and very modern and quite spacious for central Paris. The location is super convenient: only 10mins on metro from gare du nord if coming on the Eurostar and only a 20min walk into central Paris (Louvre/Notre Dame etc.). The breakfast is really good quality and the restaurant/bar is really nice spot to relax in! I would definitely recommend!

I would have given Maison Breguet a better mark except for one thing -- the extortionate, completely unjustified cost of the taxi service that the hotel uses. DO NOT ORDER A TAXI via the front desk: we were charged 65 Euros for a taxi from Gare du Nord to the hotel (3kms)... the standard price is 15-20 Euros. If the hotel doesn't want to put guests off from the start, I suggest they change their taxi service. This one is a big rip-off. Apart from that one sour, opening note, everything else about this excellent boutique hotel is very agreeable; lovely, modern rooms, friendly staff and a very relaxing bar and restaurant area. Great breakfast too. In addition the hotel offers a lap swimming pool and a gym, plus (rather expensive) massages and other treatments.

My family and I thoroughly enjoyed our stay at Maison Breguet! I have to give a huge shoutout to Sonia. I am gluten free and she went out of her way to have the hotel source incredible gluten bread for me for breakfast, a complete surprise. She also researched restaurants close by that would have dishes for me to eat. The rooms were tidy and comfortable and the shower is hands down the best I've ever had! We enjoyed our stay and would highly recommend!

Maison Breguet was perfect. A great attention to hosts, details and design make the staying unforgettable. The spa included is perfect to rest after visiting the city. I really recommend it to live a wonderful experience in Paris. It is in the heart of one of the most beautiful areas to visit.

This was our second stay at Maison Bréguet, but the first after Covid. When you dream of a hotel for your stay in Paris, this property is that dream incarnate. The rooms are beautifully appointed with comfortable beds and MUCH nicer pillows than one usually finds in hotels these days. The staff could not be more friendly and helpful. The restaurant where breakfast is served daily is a sight to see, in itself — and you get to start every day there. If you stay here and decide you still want to venture out into the city that awaits beyond the hotel entrance, you will be well-pleased with the hotel’s location: on the eastern edge of the Marais, in the 11th, several metro lines are only a short walk. And, venturing farther into the 11th, you’ll discover many superb, off-the-beaten-tourist-path restaurants. We cannot wait to book our next stay here.

Lovely hotel, charming staff and great location close to the Opera Bastille and Notre Dame. We had a wonderful weekend stay and were made to feel most welcome. That says it all so I have nothing to add!

Warm, friendly staff. Sparkly, opulent but understated design. Laid-back luxury. Super comfortable beds and beautiful bathrooms. Stylish bar area for a drink in the evening. Walkable to the Marais districts and near lots of great, small restaurants. We loved everything about MB and will be back!

We stayed for one night in November 2021 and it could not have been better. The hotel’s design is beautiful and well thought out, the staff are friendly and efficient, and the breakfast was delicious. The spa is quiet and calming and was a real bonus too, and we slept very well on the comfy bed. Thank you Maison Bréguet!

Fantastic hotel, great service, very high standard, great location, great restaurant, very quiet rooms with comfortable beds and top toiletries. Great spa, lovely breakfast, I would definitely recommend .

The location of the hotel is very good. The rooms are spacious, clean and very confortable. I was particularly impressed with the great service by everyone. The breakfast buffet was good with a lot of options.

Me and my kids love this hotel. The staff are so friendly and down to earth. Amazing stay!! Food from breakfast to dinner was good and price was reasonable. The pool area was clean and having the sauna next to the pool allowed me to supervised my kids while they were swimming.

Would only give 3 star Basic . Should be maximum 4 star. Pretends to be 5 star hotel. Damp room. Smells bad. Would not recommend . I am only writing more words as review must be more than 200 words . Really would snot recommend . Go to thibourg or grand boulevards for better quality for the same price. Do not go here .

We had made this booking pre-Covid and prepaid everything. We then had to postpone the trip twice until we could finally travel in October 2021. The hotel is quite new, rooms are nice and quite spacious.
When checking out the receptionists could not find the vouchers - I was treated like I was trying to cheat them - I had to retrieve the payment receipts from my credit card to convince them though they had all our e-mails in their system. They made us wait 20 minutes and did not really bither to apologize. Incompetence and bad service!

Beautifully designed hotel. Every detail observed. Service was top notch. The restaurant had a wonderful Sunday brunch. Beds were amazingly comfortable, as good as I’ve ever experienced. Especially fun were the trompe l’oeil tiles in the bathroom. Indoor pool, sauna, and steam room were immaculate.

I had an amazing stay at Maison Bréguet.

The hotel is very well located in the heart of 11th district which is one of the most lively neighborhood in Paris.

The hotel provides all the comfort you need, the rooms are wide, sunny and designed with taste. The breakfast is very well furnished and the staff is very helpful and welcoming.

Thanks !

Lolita_Rose

I booked 3 rooms at 6th floor from Thursday July 1 to Sunday July 4.

Friday morning at 11.00 I asked a Capuccino, it wasn’t possible because the washing machine wasn’t working then they weren’t able to make coffees and capuccinos (5 stars hotel???).

Friday afternoon I came back to the Hotel, being hungry, I asked something to eat, maybe a sandwich. They answered it was impossible because the kitchen opens at 7.00 PM (5 stars hotel???).

Since Saturday afternoon till at least Sunday morning, the elevator serving the 6th floor didn’t work, obliging us to use the stairs (5 stars hotel???).

Sunday morning, we asked to take the luggages down, they said to help ourselves (5 stars hotel???).

All the 3 rooms had the TVs not working, not even connected to the antenna, cable or internet (5 stars hotel???).

In the restaurant, staff speaking among them, with no attention to the client and a noisy cleaning was done during the business hours within hotel clients (5 stars hotel??).

For sure I paid a bill of a 5 stars hotel, for sure I didn’t receive the services I paid for.

Stayed 2 nights at the hotel with my partner. During these two days we had to chase the reception multiple times staring from the amenities the housekeeping forgot to re-fill and ending with the breakfast menu and the breakfast itself. Needless to say, even after me reporting the issue, the resolution took significant amount of time and multiple reminders. I understand perhaps the service has been affected by Covid-19, although I have not noticed the new discounted rates to reflect the service levels.
The restaurant is closed for obvious reasons, in room dining has extremely limited options: burger (steak) + french fries or pasta, no garnish, no vegetables.
And God forbid to forget something in the hotel, no “lost & found” service, the items just disappear.

Do not recommend.

This is not a five star hotel, it is a four. The rooms are small and noisy, the bedding cheap and synthetic, the breakfast is disappointing. The service from some of the staff is excellent, from others indifferent. It looks nice, nice fixtures and fittings, it is stylish but I am afraid it is all style and no substance. There are far better offerings than this in Paris and the glowing reviews genuinely puzzle me. The hotel is very clean so you cannot fault them there but if you expect a five star you will be disappointed

The decor of the hotel is amazing while the room was clean and bright, with a very comfortable bed and great little balcony, which ran the length of the room and offered a great sun trap. To escape the heat (~33° for the duration of our stay), the room also remained cool (a quite and easily controlled environmental control) and was a nice contrast to the heat outside.

The bathroom was nice with great huge mirror and deep bath, good water pressure and a door on to the balcony.

There were also some excellent staff (George, Jadidja, Solange and Odillion - merci!). The pool and spa area were pristine and private and very much enjoyed.

It is also in a good location close to the Bastille Metro, Place des Vosages with quick and easy access to Notre Dame the Louvre et al and not overrun by tourists.

Would definitely recommend.

We stayed at Maison Breguet for our 1st Wedding Anniversary and were not disappointed. The hotel was beautiful, perfectly clean and the staff were helpful and attentive. The location being North of the Bastille was an ideal place to be located with easy access to all of Paris. The rooms were bright and airy with everything you could need and the complimentary breakfast was fantastic and set us up for the day. I would definitely recommend this hotel if you are looking for a romantic break in Paris.

Nice room (even if there is no tea pot) and good receptions but we have a very bad experience. First we asked for a blanket because it was super cold in the room and it took more than 1 hour and 2 calls to obtain it (well, we did not get a blanket but a duvet...). The breakfast was an unbelievable experience. It took us 1.30h to finish...the pastries arrived at the end when we already finished everything, a few orders arrived wrong, we ordered a matcha latte from the menu and they said they did not know how to do it. There were only 4 tables with people and everybody had to wait hours to get it...unbelievable for a "5-stars" hotel. I cannot even imagine when the hotel is at full capacity. In addition, they have a restaurant (even if the menu is the poorest I have ever seen) but no in-room dining. You can order breakfast, but nothing else. This is not acceptable. Honestly, i would not rate it more than 3 stars hotel, even if the price is definetely 5stars. And to conclude, while I am writing this, I am still waiting for towels and toilet papers (which they forgot to let in the room while cleaining)...30 min has passed so far.

Stayed here for the weekend, really enjoyed it. The hotel is beautiful and there were various options for breakfast (we didn't have dinner there). Very close to a metro station and we didn't feel as if we were too far from attractions.
The only downfall was when booking, they asked for our arrival time so that our room could be ready for when we got there, however, it was not and we couldn't check-in for a few hours (they did keep our bags though, which was nice).

We planned to visit this hotel from 4th - 8th March as part of our holiday in Europe. My partner fell ill in London and was checked into hospital for 2.5 days. We were unable to travel to Paris and contacted the hotel to let them know we weren’t coming and requested a refund on compassionate grounds given the circumstances. The hotel responded with a flat out no. To make matters worse, while I was trying to organize emergency accommodation in London this hotel sneakily charged our credit card again even though we had already paid in full (they have since cancelled the double charge but when you are scrambling to find emergency accommodation this is unwelcomed and not helpful at all).
Totally disappointed. For all the great reviews, they have no compassion whatsoever.

A gem of hotel, ideally located and with exquisite premises. The rooms were spacious and fresh in beautiful surroundings. We were very pleased with the generous breakfast, fun apéro and dinner. The team were so welcoming and happy to help!

The hotel is relatively new so everything is clean and looks good. There is some variation in room size and quality but overall standard very high. Staff tries hard to please but isn’t always given authority to do anything by senior management (especially if there are problems with room etc). However a real standout on our trip was night receptionist Richard Mocque who went above and beyond the call of duty numerous times to ensure we had an enjoyable stay. It is rare to meet such kind and helpful people in the hospitality industry nowadays given how busy everyone is and how hard it is to give personalised attention to everyone. We hugely appreciated meeting Richard and he really made our stay go from good to great.

Bold three rooms for three nights.
Obtained a Really good rate by walking in on a previous visit to Paris in November.
Room rate to nicked breakfast was about 157 Euros per night to include breakfast.
Parking in Street is very expensive -about €80 per day but hotel will let a couple of cars park in front without paying.
Staff are very welcoming particularly Erick during the day and Richard a night.
Very nice restaurant and bar.
Complimentary tea/coffee and cakes every afternoon.
Very nice touch.
Band new Spa,Pool,Gym,Sauna and Steamroom.
All n immaculate condition.
Standard rooms are well equipped but very small.
My Son was put into a duplex with a balcony -very nice.
Breakfast was more than adequate.Dinner was excellent -about €60 per head to include a bottle of wine.
Great location -would definitely return.

We arrived in Paris very late in the evening (around 10.30pm) with a very tired, hangry 6 year old in tow. Initially we were disappointed that the kitchen had closed and we weren't able to get any room service meals brought up to us - given that it was a 5-star hotel. But our lovely concierge immediately recommended a lovely restaurant nearby Le Petite Marche and rang them to ask for a table for us which they had - thank you because the meal was amazing! The hotel room was lovely and clean with beautiful products in the bathroom. The pool was lovely and our son really enjoyed swimming in there the following day. Breakfast was also lovely but it was a little disorganised. It wasn't clear where to sit, or where to order, coffee ran out the two mornings we were there and it took ages for them to remake. That said, the pancakes were lovely. Overall the hotel was lovely, and the only reason it gets four stars instead of five is the breakfast and room service glitches which I'm sure could be quickly improved :). Apart from that - a really enjoyable stay - thank you!

Stayed in the Maison Breguet last weekend with my son... in short I can’t fault the hotel!! For a start the staff were very welcoming, friendly and super helpful from the start of the trip until the end. The bedrooms and bathrooms are elegant and comfortable with everything you need. The restaurant and spa lived up to our expectation as well. The location is great, we walked everywhere including to the Louvre, Pere Lachaise, and the Accor arena. The surrounding streets are full of restaurants and bars to suit every taste. Really hope we get the chance to return soon. Thank you Maison Breguet

The hotel is absolutely gorgeous and situated in a perfect part of town. It felt central to everything we wanted to do in the Bastille area. Additionally, the staff is very friendly and eager to make your stay as comfortable as possible. I hope to return soon!

A wonderfully elegant but unpretentious hotel with an incredible restaurant. A little off the beaten path, but still convenient. High end interiors with so much style! The tassled key fobs are just one of many details that add to the ambience. Wonderful soaps and potions from Maison Margiela are simply too luxurious for words. The staff is quite professional without being stiff or overly formal. The pool is not large but the perfect size to escape the bustle and grime after a long day of exploring the Paris streetscape. I stay at this hotel every chance I get. 4 times in the past 2 years.

The staff and rooms were wonderful. They spent quite a bit of time working with us to make certain every need and request was met or exceeded. We were traveling with two teenagers and they arranged for us to have adjoining rooms.

There was a transportation strike (it’s is Paris - strikes happen), and they had to scramble to make certain everything was in order. But everything went off without a hitch.

Breakfast buffet was plentiful and delicious even on Xmas morning!

Really a wonderful place. We will certainly be back.

This hotel really needs a good manager. It is clearly seen that nobody is seriously concerned with the the guests comfort.
The room was never clean. The rug under a bed is so dirty that it is disgusting!! The floor was never cleaned properly.
At the breakfast everything is badly organized, plates were never taken from us and we needed to put them at the other tables to have space.
We asked for oatmeal porridge and people could not even understand what we are talking about! The whole world eats it but not here!!! In one hotel where we once stayed they just went and buy it and cooked!! I left a small bag there and never got it
back.
Lot of things should be fixed there. A heating system did not work properly. The restaurant at the hotel did not work for couple of days at all.
And the most upsetting thing. We did not have internet for three days because the technician did not come. Seriously? As the result we have to pay for the roaming because we needed to work and be connected.
The manager is coming to work at 11 o’clock!!
May be she can try to get up earlier??

A very cute hotel with nice decor and good service! The hotel is also in a central location, very walkable to major sightseeing spots. The only bad thing was that the bed was not super comfortable to me

Recent, small structure, with personality, good interior design level, attention to detail.
Quiet and functional (including bed comfort).
Adequate services, even the small spa, considering the overall size.
Very nice young staff.
Limits (compatible with the proposed prices, Paris standard):
- room and bathroom size and equipment contained;
- limited restaurant service hours (but good breakfast).
Great location: Bastille, Le Marais, public transport, Gare de Lyon not far away.
Valid quality/price ratio.

Maison Breguet is a stylish boutique hotel located in the 11 district.
My friend and I stayed in a junior suite.

+ : Room was spacious and nicely decorated. Bed was comfy, bathroom was very clean and had nice amenities from Maison Margiela. A complementary bottle of water and a Nespresso coffee maker were part of the perks of staying in a junior suite. Reception staff as well as the staff at the bar and the restaurant were super friendly and accomodating.
Drinks and food at the restaurant were good as well as the complementary breakfast.

- : airconditioning didn't work because of the fact that it's centralized, our bathroom had a bath which was too small for myself as well as for my friend (and we're both only between 1m76 and 1m81), the showerhose in the bathtub leaked water from the back and the shower door, which was installed in the bath, wasn't big enough so the bathroom floor was soaking wet every time we took a shower. There weren't enough racks in the bathroom either to hang all of our wet towels on.
Carpets in the room were nice, but we were not sure if they were clean.

All in all we had a nice stay in a very good hotel, but some things could have been better.

I just returned from a four night stay at the Maison Breguet. If you are expecting a solid 4 star hotel Breguet will be perfect for you. Somehow it is ranked as a 5 star hotel and if you expect a 5 star experience you will be pretty disappointed. The positive. The hotel is in a great location. Just about a 7 minute walk to the Marais, close to the hip Oberkampf area and near to the Bastille subway hub. The hotel is nicely designed. The restaurant is lovely and the rooms are clean and quiet. The bathroom is spacious and the bed very comfortable. We booked adjacent single rooms attached by a small vestibule which was a perfect arrangement.
On the less positive side -- Some of the front desk staff were great but overall it was pretty uneven. When we asked for a dinner recommendation the front desk had one recommendation -- the hotel. The rest he said were far away and $150 euros. Really? We walked over to the Marais and had a wonderful meal, 60 euros for two. At breakfast we asked for cappuccinos and the waitress showed me the coffee machine and the milk dispenser. Also the buffet was limited and not fabulous. I'd say skip the breakfast (we had it included in our rate), but the streets immediately adjacent to the hotel do not have a lot of food choices so it may be the best breakfast option despite it's flaws.
Despite some shortcomings the hotel is a good one and I would visit again, particularly if I was looking for single rooms at a good value.

Just returned from a weeks stay at this beautiful hotel. The staff could not have been more professional/helpful. Its in a great location, down a nice quiet street but with plenty of great bistro's bars in the neighbourhood and everything is in walking distance. The bedrooms are beautifully appointed with Maison Margiela toiletries (shampoo, conditioner, and body cream!) The pool and spa area was spotlessly clean and the perfect place top chill out and have a swim/steam in the morning. There is complementary afternoon tea in the bar every day which was nice added extra! They also have complementary use of some bicycles which was also a great extra!

Really nice boutique hotel in a cool area, walking distance to the Marais and all the cool spots in Bastille. Bastille and République train station 2 mins walk away. Lively bars and restaurants close by.

Exceptionally clean and comfortable rooms with a night time chocolates left on your pillow for a personal touch! The showers could be better designed. Bathroom amenities include hairdryer and Maison Margiela toiletries. In room nespresso machine.

Breakfast service and options are good (pastries, cereal, fruit, pancakes, hot eggs cooked how you would like, cold meats and cheeses to name a few items).

Good sauna and pool. Only drawback was the air con in the fitness room is centralised so you couldn’t adjust the temp. Fitness room comprised of a treadmill, elliptical machine and bench/weights.

Special mention to the lovely doorman who was very helpful and full of smiles.

The warm and gracious staff made us feel so at home! The location was great for our explorations of Paris. The room was cozy, but very well appointed and comfortable. The breakfast was a delicious and satisfying. We would definitely recommend this hotel! Merci beaucoup!

While on the recent week stay in Paris for a writing retreat I had the pleasure to stay at Maison Breguet. It was a wonderful experience. A beautiful boutique hotel in an arty area, the rooms were quiet, comfortable and clean, the decoration quirky and stylish, the restaurant a wonderful place to start with breakfast and retire to after a busy day, and the small spa and fitness area a nice relaxing place to retreat to. A wonder stay in the busy capital and I fully recommend it. The staff were particularly helpful and when I accidentally left earrings that I purchased at a shop some distance away on my last day in Paris, they organised to have them picked up and couriered back to me in Australia. Wonderful people. Definitely will be visiting again.

What a find. Small hotel with reasonable prices in a busy but non-touristy area near the Bastille. Comfy rooms and great service, with a beautiful atrium lounge/restaurant that was a welcome retreat in the mornings and evenings. Would absolutely stay hear again.

Very sad to say that this boutique hotel has little sympathy for medical/family emergencies. Needed to shorten, NOT cancel my stay, due to a serious medical/childcare emergency. I called 1 day after booking, two weeks before the arrival date, a $4.6K stay for 9 days when the emergency occurred. Since they are fully booked and it is Paris Fashion Week, they could easily rebook the room. I feel they are taking advantage of my predicament. They hung up on the platinum travel service I had booked with and never called back as promised to respond to my request when I called less than 24 hours of booking.

For a quiet and private stay in a 5 star boutique hotel, pick Maison Breguet. Charming, and thoughtful hotel design, it’s located in the 11th arrondissement, near Marais, and Canal Saint Martin, away from the tourists and near local shops.

The guy that checked us in was amazing. He met us outside and took our bags in Only 1 of the ladies was not very nice and she was the one with the crook in her neck. Everyone else was super nice and hotel was amazing. I would go back and just ignore her. She even talked about us in French but I pretended to not understand.

Had a great stay here with my kids. Really cool design throughout and edgy up and coming neghbourhood - saw a steady stream of people emerging from a nightclub at 9am on the Wednesday AM. My kids loved the swimmming pool in the spa not sure the honeymooning couples may have felt the same way. Proper blackout curtains meant the kids slept in until nearly 9am allowing me to get a couple of hours work out the way in the AM. Great turn down service with really tasty chocolate. Could not fault any of it other than not being able to work the in room air con (which was way too cold) but this was probably due to my technical incompetence. Nothing was ever more than a 30 min metro ride / walk or 10E uber. Finally fell in love with Paris and this hotel had a lot to do with it. Solid restaurant which will review seperately which was surprisingly empty. Highly recommended.

I stayed for 2 nights with my 6 year old son.
We used the swimming pool in the morning. Excellent. Got out of bed and popped down for swim.
Breakfast was good too. A nice atmosphere. Plenty of options. Also, a menu if more was needed. Poached eggs etc.
The area is good. I don’t know Paris very well.
There’s a metro 5 minutes walk. Lots of bars, restaurants and shops.
A nice area of Paris.
I’m a genuine tourist and father with son from Scotland. We really enjoyed the hotel and the surroundings.

An excellent boutique hotel. Beautifully designed 1930’s style Art Deco interior - very classy. The rooms are gorgeous and functional. The staff are polite, professional and friendly. The restaurant food is fresh and delicious. I would definitely stay at Masion Breguet again - I’m a very happy customer! 😊
Special appreciation to:
Erick
Eva
Mohammed
And kitchen staff in breakfast / dinner for amazing food.

Tips
Get the Deluxe room as opposed to a superior room - Deluxe has a large king size bed and the room / bathroom is slightly bigger.
Metro is line 5 from Gare du Norde (about 5 / 6 stops). Get off at Saint Sabin exit 1 - this is the closest exit to the hotel which is about a 2min walk from this exit.
Bastille market on Thursday & Sunday morning is worth the visit even just to see all the produce.

We had connecting rooms for our family of two adults and two young children. Very convenient. The rooms were a bit small but the design and the pool and the staff made more than well up for that! Restaurant was excellent (good wines!) and the breakfast was also very good.

Excellent service and hotel quality that meets 5* standards and can compete with any larger hotel chain. However, here you get the true experience of Paris and individual client service without the anonymity of a large 5*!!

Our family (2 adults and 2 kids) stayed here for a couple of nights visiting Paris. The rooms were great. We had a suite-style room with two connecting rooms, one with a king and the other with two tweens, both with bathrooms. The beds were very comfortable and the shower was amazing, really strong water pressure! There is a pool and spa but we didn’t get to use them in just a couple of days. Location is great. Quiet part of the city but easy to get around with metro lines 1, 5, and 8 within a 10 minute walk. We actually walked all the way back from the Arc de Triomphe, via the Louvre, and Notre Dame (currently closed due to the fire). It took a couple of hours but definitely doable. Definitely recommended!

Nice week in Paris! Great hotel and my dog was very welcome! The staff was very friendly and the rooms were very clean. The deining pool was beautiful and very relaxing! This hotel made my stay in Paris amazing!

Maison Breguet is a gem. I'm in Paris fairly often, and can't really imagine booking anywhere else now. Shame there's no loyalty scheme. Hint hint.

The look that most up-market hotels these days seem to be targetting is a sort of brown soft cavern, as though the decorating had been performed entirely using a muscavado-filled pipe bomb. Bregeut avoids this. The rooms are light and airy, sparely and tastefully decorated. We had a charming junior suite which had something of the feel of a conservatory nestled on the top of the building. The plants were missing, but the ambience remained. I liked it a lot, and so did my son. The balcony was a decent size, and while the view was nothing to write a review about, it was inoffensive.

The bathroom was good; it was an unusual configuration with a sort of bathroom-cum-baggage-room-cum-dressing room in addition to the main bedroom bit, but it worked well and felt spacious. I don't remember anything about the plumbing, which is a Good Sign. I did manage to spray water all over the floor, but I do that just about everywhere, so I don't blame the architect for my transgression.

The whole building is very pleasantly decorated; hot-air-balloon wallpaper and a cheery green courtyard. In places it feels like it needs a bit a of a facelift already, which does not speak to great build quality since it's still fairly new: walls are starting to scuff and the air conditioning drips tears of regret. Hotel proprietors of the world take note: there is no need for air conditioning anywhere north of Rome. Stop it.

The food was solid but unspectacular. My poached egg was a little vinegary for my taste and I have one more serious quibble: I do not want to be making my own tea and coffee at breakfast in a five star hotel. To make me drink nespresso is cruel, but to make me queue up to do so, standing listlessly with capsule in hand like a supplicant, seems unusual.

So why a rating of excellent? Two reasons:

Firstly, the pool: A single glowing swimlane bored into the rock that makes you feel like you're in the lair of a Bond-film villain. It's all very plush, with loads fluffy towels and bottles of chilled water on hand. There's a steam room and sauna and it's usually pretty quiet. My son couldn't get enough of it.

Secondly, the service: Paris is a city which is famous for many things. I will risk the wrath of the Parisians by suggesting that neither service nor courtesy is one of them. There are exception of course, and at Bregeut they have somehow corralled a large number of those exceptions into a small place and kept them there. The service was unfailingly courteous, and often downright friendly. We felt very welcome.

In summary, Maison Bregeut is a joy. I recommend it wholeheartedly! If they stopped serving nespresso at breakast it would be close to perfect.

We stayed four nights at the Maison Bréguet and took advantage of the wonderful breakfast, afternoon coffee, and sauna/steam/lap pool every day. My daughter loved the pool and the made to order pancakes. The staff was friendly, courteous, and extremely helpful. The rooms were large for Parisian standards and the bathroom was a DREAM! We had connecting rooms with our own little hallway, perfect for a family. My daughter (and I) thought the bed was one of the most comfortable we had ever slept on. Walkable to all sites in the center of Paris. Would heartily recommend! The only issue we had was that two of our four days, the room was not cleaned when we were back at the hotel around 4:30. Thank you to all the wonderful staff!

We had an excellent stay at Maison Breguet. Service was excellent from everyone there. Food from the restaurant was delicious. Our room was very lovely and for such a great value. Amazing bonus to be able to star and moon gaze from our bed through the skylights in our junior suite.

Nice hotel, very helpful front office staff. Breakfast is OK, service is lacking. Restaurant had good food for dinner. Many small restaurants in the neighborhood and organic food store around the corner. Getting downtown by Uber was not very fast, better Is to use public transport like Metro which is close by.

+
Friendly and professional reception. Nothing was too much trouble.
Huge and tasty selection of both hot and cold breakfast offered by very helpful staff.
Modern, cool and elegantly furnished.
-
Small and cramped bedroom.

Laurent and Francesco really made the stay for our curios and conversational 6 year-old fantastic. They were engaging, friendly and super helpful to all of our wishes.

Great neighborhood too. Easy access to all the tourist sites, but enough off of the beaten path to experience real Paris culture.

Everything was fantastic! The entire staff took care of us right from the beginning. We got upgraded into a super nicely designed room, Erik was amazingly helpful and Julie was super friendly with us and our little baby. The hotel is conveniently located and quiet. Highly recommend it!

We travel a fair amount as a family in Europe and this place stacks up against the best. Awesomely staff (speak English), good onsite restaurant, walking distance to restaurants and subway. We’d return for sure. Great adjoining rooms for us a family of four. Only two knocks against would be no desk in the room and while the cleaning service was high quality it wasn’t always timely. Nevertheless, a wonderful place in which we built lasting memories.

Great Hotel, perfect location and pleasant staff (especially Laurent)
Highly recommend staying at Maison Breguet. Spacious and quiet room very nicely decorated. Margiela toiletries are definetly a plus !

Very nice, modem, boutique and cosy hotel close to Bastille. Staff very helpful. Great atmosphere resembling a bit of the soho house style. Great cocktails. Stayed just one night but will definitely come back again.
